
Overview of noun trigger

The noun trigger has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (5) gun trigger, trigger -- (lever that activates the firing mechanism of a gun)
2. trigger -- (a device that activates or releases or causes something to happen)
3. trigger, induction, initiation -- (an act that sets in motion some course of events)

Overview of verb trigger

The verb trigger has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (4) trip, actuate, trigger, activate, set off, spark off, spark, trigger off, touch off -- (put in motion or move to act; "trigger a reaction"; "actuate the circuits")
2. (1) trigger -- (release or pull the trigger on; "Trigger a gun")
